It is the aim of this paper to point out that occur in some risks practicing the psychotherapeutic profession. This topic will be exemplified by studying the values and ideologies of psychotherapists and their influence on patients as well as by presenting the problem of abuse of authority and dependency. Various explanations will be offered for these phenomena, and some possibilities of prevention of these risks will be considered. Thereby, it will be pointed especially to some deficits in the curricula of psychotherapeutic education.  
